OL,3,CExtra stop and search powers granted
OL,4,Cafter knife attack in Bristol
OL,6,F"A section 60 power authorises
OL,7,Fofficers to stop and search an
OL,8,Findividual if they have suspicions
OL,9,Fthat they may be carrying knives or
OL,10,Fother weapons which could be used in
OL,11,Fserious violence in the area.
OL,13,F"Alongside this, they will also have a
OL,14,Fsection 60AA power which allows
OL,15,Fofficers to ask people to remove face
OL,16,Fcoverings if they have reason to
OL,17,Fbelieve it is being worn to conceal
OL,18,Ftheir identity.
